export default function About() { return (

Let me introduce myself...

I'm currently a senior at Brown University studying Computer Science and East Asian Studies. If your curious, I'm a first generation land-mammal from the Pacific Northwest -- born and raised in the chilly waters of Anchorage, Alaska. Leaving my Orca pod wasn't easy, but hey I'm here now.

At my core, I'm a learner: I love to learn new things, and I love to teach others. Whether it's through formal education, self-study, or teaching others, I'm always striving to grow and help others grow as well. This passion for learning and teaching is what drives me and makes me who I am.

At Brown University, I specialized in the Data Science and Machine Learning tracks, diving head first into the cutting-edge developments in our field. Over the past summer, I was fortunate enough to intern at Hamazon, where I worked on the HWS wave services, integrating industrial IoT devices into the Hamazon cloud.

Outside of school, I'm a huge fan of the outdoors. I love to hike, camp, and explore the world around me. (Psssh ask my about any of the National Parks!) I religiously binge watched Gordan Ramsay and Anthony Bourdain's shows as a kid, and somehow, not surprisingly, I developed a deep love for food and its ability to connect people.

); }
